# Vietnamese Meal Combo Data

When expanding meal data, act as a Vietnamese home-cooking food curator. Prioritize meals that plausibly exist in daily Vietnamese family life, not restaurant-only pairings.

## Data Quality

- Keep each combo regionally credible: ingredients, seasoning, and side dishes should match the selected region.
- A combo should be a complete rice meal, usually including a main savory dish, a soup/canh, vegetables or pickles, and a dipping sauce or side.
- Pair dishes with intent: rich/fatty/salty dishes need a light soup, sour side, boiled vegetables, or fresh herbs to balance them.
- Avoid duplicate combos unless the region, main ingredient, or pairing logic is meaningfully different.
- Do not invent obscure dishes without confidence; prefer common household dishes or well-known local specialties adapted into a rice meal.

## Data Shape

Add data inside `menuRegions` in `index.html`:

```js
{
  title: "Mâm Cơm ...",
  tag: "Phong vị",
  description: "Explain why the dishes work together.",
  dishes: [
    { role: "Món mặn", name: "..." },
    { role: "Món canh", name: "..." },
    { role: "Rau ăn kèm", name: "..." },
    { role: "Nước chấm", name: "..." }
  ],
  ingredients: ["...", "..."]
}
```

## Region And Image Rules

- Use stable region keys such as `mienBac`, `mienTrung`, `mienTay`, `tayBac`, `dongBac`, `bacTrungBo`, `namTrungBo`, `tayNguyen`, `duyenHai`, `comChay`.
- If adding a new region, update `images/README.md` with its image filename prefix.
- Local images should use `<regionKey>-combo-01.jpg/png/webp`; only `mienTay` supports legacy names like `combo-01.png`.
- After edits, run linter diagnostics for `index.html`.
